caption: I miss this place so much, went there for lunch often when I worked downtown. Glad to hear it’s still there, super good and reasonably priced. Great little cucumber starter on the house, wonder if they still have that.

This restaurant is my preferred one. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this one I go the most. The crew is very cordial and the cuisine they cook is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent meal in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.

Super impressed with this local gem of a restaurant at 3 Hanover Square on Beaver Street. The sashimi was super fresh, the gyozo to die for. Lots of little extras come with. Lovely service. I highly recommend it as your local Japanese (especially now that Haru has closed.
Food is ok, but service is weird, no signs about additional Covid charged... so basically for regular bento box and one portion of regular rolls and two pints of beer you have to pay $75+ tips
Food is amazing... probably best sushi in all of NYC (certainly my favorite). Service is exceptional and staff extremely friendly.
EXCELLENT loved the food. It was so fresh and had complimentary fruit which was so good. Would recommend and I’m celiac and they accommodated my needs.

I am sorry but it is the end of my patience with Taste Of Tokyo. After being a loyal customer for about a year I have noticed how the quality is going down every single month. This is disrespectful. A few months ago they started adding cucumber to every roll as a filler, even though cucumber isn’t mentioned on the menu. Tonight I ordered a Philadelphia roll which is supposed to be cream cheese with salmon and look what they gave me. There appeared to be a tiny sliver of salmon but when I opened up the roll it was even worse. They just put it on the top to make it look like there was salmon inside. I AM NEVER GOING TO BE BACK TO THIS PLACE AGAIN.
Great, delicious food, good prices.

Superb food, generous quantities and at a price that doesn't break the bank. Will go back.

What a gem! Husband really wanted sushi and I didn't, but we both love Japanese/Chinese food. You are greeted with wet towels to wash you hands off before you eat, menu is extensive with great prices, good was phenomenal and came out fast, sake selection is amazing and very well priced, and then you are given a plate of honeydew to finish off your meal.  Someone commented that the seats are torn, and they are, but the food and service compensate for it.
Gyoza was perfectly fried. Crazy tuna roll was amazing. Very cheap for the area and the quality. Will definitely be back.
The food is consistently fresh and yummy, cashiers hands out awesome service. I love how neat it is and ambience. Will visit here again.
My go to sushi spot for lunch. Great price (dine out only) and quality sushi!
A small, quiet (on a Friday eve) spot for  shumai, sushi and Asahi beer. Service is friendly and efficient. What's not to like?

The seats are torn and filthy, the salad is not fresh, the salmon teriyaki was so not fresh and such a small portion.  The serving staff is unkempt and you get the feeling you're eating in a hospital cafeteria.  They can afford to be clean and serve fresh food.  It looks like the sushi, maybe, is the only safe thing to eat.  Will not go again.

The place is in a nice environment. The food is great. Fast service and very friendly and polite. All my coworkers usually eat there but this is my first and is not going to be last. Looking forward to going again soon. ❤🌟❤🌟❤🌟❤🌟❤🌟
Great lunch spot. The wait can be long but you can wait outside and the staff will bring your food out to you. They're also very friendly and will recognize frequent visitors!

Great service. They always look out for you and the food quality is extremely tasty.

The price point is great, but the food is only average. I ordered one of the combination specials that came with three different spicy rolls (spicy tuna roll, spicy salmon roll, and spicy yellowtail roll); in total, I got 18 pieces of sushi roll, salad, and miso soup for $16, which is a great value. Unfortunately, the spicy rolls did not live up to their name; they were not spicy at all. The atmosphere is typical of a hole-in-the-wall restaurant; upstairs where we were seated were palates of soda and other miscellaneous things strewn over half of the tables in the dining area. We ended up here because we were too tired to walk more than a block from our hotel, but I wouldn't come here again.
Great place for a bit of Tokyo in the oldest part of NYC. Get the jalapeno yellowtail as an app, it was 👌

My goto place when downtown. Good quality food and great fast service.

This is a Chinese owned sushi shop, so if you want authentic go elsewhere, for starters.  Summary: it's bad.  The worse offense was bad rice. I can forgive sub-par fish if the sushi rice is good. But the rice was sad. The ginger was bad. The interior is ugly and work down, and not in a charming way. Literally the only good thing was the service.  People, yes, I get it. It's sort of cheap. But it's bad sushi. Just pay more and get more actually good sushi.  I wish I could just block all reviews by everyone who gave this place three or more stars, I'd get much better results for food across the city.  Everyone who actually thinks this is good sushi: your taste is bad and you should feel bad.

Moderately priced, friendly staff, great staff and great food. What more could you ask for? And they do take out as well. There are three excellent places within 5 minutes of my office and 95% of the time this is the place I go.

This place is good if you want to have a quick and good  Japanese meal in the city . The fried rice is really good and so is the rock shrimp appetizer . Not too crazy about their rolls but they're raw fish is very good I usually get the yellowtail very good and fresh :)

Nice location makes it good place for lunch. Bento box has everything it should though the price is a bit high. It has very tight paths between tables but it still doable to reach the place. Even though there is not much place inside we still did not wait in line to be seated.

This is one of our favorites in the neighborhood. The food is really tasty, fast and cheap. Crab tempura is excellent as are all of the rolls, especially the rock and roll, which really does cool stuff with salmon skin. My wife and I come here at least once a week and are always happy.

I won't order from them again. They lied to me about how they prepared a meal. I asked if the meat was cooked on a grill with grill markings for flavor on the meat. When the food arrived it was crappy pan seared with no grill markings and the sauce was watery and tasteless right down to the food being presented on bean sprouts. How tasteless are bean sprouts compared to a simple standard onion. Not worth your time or money!!!!

Very affordable and tastes good. There's booth seating for about 15 people max, and you can either order at the counter for hot plates or grab from the selection of sushi in the fridge. Prepackaged for the fast paced, grab and go, quick lunch. Don't expect decor, it's small and convenient.

Quick and easy takeout sushi. Not the best I've ever had but not the worst either. We got the lunch special (2 or 3 order) and it satisfied the sushi craving. Tip! Lunch special is only for takeout/delivery. You can't eat there and have the lunch special.

For affordable sushi in the Wall Street area I go here. During lunch time this place is always packed and a lot of people will order to pick up. I happen to be one of those people, but I've noticed whenever I go there to pick up my lunch. The sushi is fresh and you can't beat their prices. Also their bento box lunch specials are good too. I've has the chicken teriyaki and chicken tempura bento box and I enjoyed both of them. The bento boxes are very filling so order it when you're really hungry.
